The only good think I can say is they were quick with food and they pile your plate up and prices are reasonable.. but the food quality was  it up to par for me and therefore I will not return .. the baked beans had a chili bean flavor which I did not like the chicken was dry and cold and they forgot to give me barbecue sauce (which was the main reason I went there and I had to drive all the way back to get it because if I didn’t I would have thrown the whole plate away. the potatoe salad had a good taste. Overall I don’t feel like this was good ole home made food which is what I had hoped it would be.. and the barbecue sauce tasted like A1 sauce ketchup and werchashure sauce and it was red.. no sweetness at all.  I just really wish it was better they seemed like sweet people in there.  He needs to just revise his recipes and put more heart in them not just throw something together.

If I could give a zero star, I would.  I have eaten ribs, both pork and beef, from all over the U.S,  and these, by far, are the worst I've ever eaten.  Dry, tough, no taste.  The BBQ sauce doesn't even make them palatable.  Don't give me the excuse of COVID because they remain open.  I would NEVER recommend Jay's Barbecue to anyone, even if I didn't like them.  TERRIBLE!!

I know some people were whining about the sauce,but Jay's BBQ has been a family owned business for 65 years. Had the exact same sauce that they have served forever. Jay's is a a Baton Rouge landmark. The food is all prepared on site, and made to order. The pork is my favorite! And you can always get the sauce on the side. The service is good and the place is well run by the 3rd generation of the family.

Anyone who thinks this is a home cooked meal is either related to the owners or have been in a turkish prison for the last 50 years. These people at Jay's aren't even trying. All the food is low grade, walmart burgers, canned beans, kraft mac and cheese. This stuff is beyond terrible. I ordered a two meat bbq plate and got some sloppy joe stuff that was suppose to be bbq beef and the pork was thin as paper towel and had zero flavor, zero texture....how can they think this is legit bbq? No cuts of meat. Canned bbq sauce (kraft). Wth. They not even trying to deliver a decent meal and had the nerve to charge me 16 dollars for a lunch I could have gotten at any middle school free lunch program. Wow is all I have to say. These people either no nothing about the restaurant business or are too stoopid to understand what a real meal is. Pathetic!
